## File Organization

### New Components
- UI primitives → `/src/components/ui/`
- Dashboard features → `/src/components/dashboard/`
- Layout components → `/src/components/layout/`

### Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `AssetCard.tsx`)
- Utilities: camelCase (e.g., `utils.ts`)
- Types/Interfaces: PascalCase with prefix (e.g., `IAssetData`, `TAssetType`)

## Code Style Rules

### TypeScript
- Always define proper types for props
- Use interface for component props
- Export component and types together

```tsx
interface AssetCardProps {
  title: string;
  thumbnail: string;
  aspectRatio: "16:9" | "9:16" | "1:1" | "4:5";
  isFavorite?: boolean;
  onFavoriteClick?: () => void;
}

export function AssetCard({ title, thumbnail, aspectRatio, isFavorite = false, onFavoriteClick }: AssetCardProps) {
  // ...
}
```

### Component Structure
```tsx
// 1. Imports (React, external libs, internal components, utils, types)
// 2. Types/Interfaces
// 3. Variants (CVA) if applicable
// 4. Component function
// 5. Exports
```

## DO's and DON'Ts

### DO
- Use existing UI components from `/src/components/ui/`
- Follow the 8px spacing grid
- Use the exact color values from the palette
- Use `cn()` for conditional classes
- Maintain dark theme as primary
- Use Lucide icons consistently
- Keep components small and focused
- Use TypeScript strict mode

### DON'T
- Don't create new color values without updating the design system
- Don't use inline styles
- Don't use arbitrary Tailwind values unless matching the design tokens
- Don't ignore accessibility (use proper ARIA attributes)
- Don't use px values that don't align with 8px grid
- Don't create new typography styles outside the scale
- Don't use `!important` in Tailwind classes

## Accessibility Requirements
- All interactive elements must have focus states
- Use semantic HTML (proper heading hierarchy h1-h4)
- Buttons must have accessible names
- Color contrast ratio: minimum 4.5:1
- Touch targets: minimum 32px × 32px

